            <p>495 Lexington Ave.<lb/>
                New York&#44; 17th. Dec. 1885<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev and dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your favor of yesterday&#39;s date to<lb/> hand&#44; I beg to say that Mr. Menken has<lb/> sent me a verbal message by his son&#45;&#45;<lb/>who is in my office&#44; for the sake of the<lb/> Sabbath&#45;&#45; requesting that since I have<lb/> transmitted you a copy of his reply to<lb/> me&#44; I should let him know what you<lb/> say about it when I hear from you.<lb/> Therefore you may write him that I<lb/> have communicated the same to you&#44;<lb/> and asked you rather to correspond<lb/> directly with him.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly&#44;<lb/>
                David M. Piza<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
